[Student "S"]
{Compare this hand with Deal 6. 
NORTH has five \Ss, this time so she bids 1\S.

SOUTH knows there IS an 8-card fit in \Ss, so he bids 2\S.

NORTH has 10 points so she passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "N:KJ86.65.T832.873 A52.AQT93.97.AJ2 QT43.J2.AJ54.Q65 97.K874.KQ6.KT94"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
pass 1H 1S 2S pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "3db651b94984ca4fc5fdf310e1d48ce6cf4958f9e9087f7d627215197941d2a5"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/negative_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST has 11/12 points, a Limit Raise in \Hs. So after the overcall 
he makes a Support Cue-bid of 2\S.

EAST adds her 16 to the 11 that WEST has promised as a minimum and goes straight 
to 4\H.

If WEST had significantly more than 11 he could bid on, but in this case he should happily pass.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:AJ64.62.KJ43.J73 852.AQT93.97.AQ2 KQT3.J5.AQ52.865 97.K874.T86.KT94"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "3H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
pass 1H 1S 3H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "9e0b08d527410895a0eea4d9dbdbb5c8d505d3f5322d5f45e030bae8cced4888"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/negative_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{Compare this with Deal 8.

NORTH has 7 points, barely enough for a 2\H raise if there had been no overcall.
But when WEST puts in the \S bid, NORTH can jump to 3\H as a preemptive 
measure. He knows SOUTH won't think he has strength because he did not make a Support Cue-bid.

SOUTH does know it and passes 3\H.}

